description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for permanent Staff Nurses to join our nursing team within the surgical unit on Ward 1 on either a full or part time basis. Our Surgical ward specialises in caring for both male and female adult patients undergoing emergency surgery and those admitted with acute surgical conditions including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General Surgery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gynaecology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minor orthopaedic conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our nursing teams are focussed on the six C’s, and we aim to provide a high quality service in a safe environment where the needs of each patient are cared for in a professional and holistic manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will possess excellent communication skills, team working skills and some knowledge of surgical procedures to join our busy units. We will support your development in the post through personal development planning, excellent training opportunities and will support you to broaden your experience, skills and knowledge in the rotation into the surgical ward areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer flexible working patterns on a roster basis which includes a well-balanced combination of days, nights and weekends in order to meet the needs of our patients and provide a fair and equal working environment for the whole team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information on the Trust please visit our website using the link on the right hand side.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week: full time &amp; part time hours available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift pattern: shifts will be either early (7:00-15:00), late (13:00-20:00), long day (7:00-20:00) or night shifts (19:30-7:30)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For details about the role and ward/informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mel Pearson&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Sister Ward 1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;01625 661001&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For queries regarding the application and or interview process, please contact the Recruitment Team either via email, ecn-tr.recruitment@nhs.net or telephone, 01625 656510&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We would like to inform you that if your application is successful, your interview will be held via SKYPE.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
